1 (iii) Talbot County, from 30 minutes before sunrise until 10:30 a.m.
2 [(7)] (8) Notwithstanding any other provision of this subtitle, the
3 Department may allow a person with a deer management permit to shoot deer on any
4 Sunday throughout the year in accordance with the terms of the permit.
5 [(8)] (9) The Department may allow a person using a State certified
6 raptor to hunt game birds or mammals on each Sunday during the open season for the
7 game birds or mammals.
8 [(9)] (10) The Department may allow an unarmed person participating in
9 an organized fox chase to chase foxes on Sunday.
10 [(10)] (11) The Department may allow a person shooting pen–reared game
11 birds or tower–released flighted mallard ducks to hunt on Sunday at a regulated shooting
12 ground in accordance with § 10–906 of this title.
13 [(11)] (12) The Department may allow a person who is 16 years old or
14 younger to hunt on Sunday if participating in a junior hunt established by the Department
15 in accordance with this subtitle.
16 [(12)] (13) Except as provided in paragraphs [(8)] (9) through [(10)] (11) of
17 this subsection and subject to paragraph [(7)] (8) of this subsection, a person may not hunt
18 on Sunday in:
19 (i) [Baltimore City;
20 (ii)] Baltimore County;
21 [(iii)] (II) Howard County; or
22 [(iv)] (III) Prince George’s County.
23 [(13)] (14) A person may not hunt migratory game birds on Sunday.
24 [(14)] (15) A person may not hunt on public land within the State park
25 system on Sunday.
