24 (g) (1) Except as provided in paragraphs (2) and (3) of this subsection, a
25 person, other than the owner or occupant, while hunting for any wild bird or mammal may
26 not shoot or discharge any firearm or other deadly weapon within 150 yards, known as the
27 “safety zone”, of a dwelling house, residence, church, or other building or camp occupied by
28 human beings, or shoot at any wild bird or mammal while it is within this area, without
29 the specific advance permission of the owner or occupant.
30 (3) (i) For archery hunters in Allegany County, BALTIMORE CITY,
31 EXCEPT IN LEGISLATIVE DISTRICT 43A, Calvert County, Carroll County, Cecil County,
32 Frederick County, Garrett County, Harford County, Montgomery County, St. Mary’s

